I put the proposition of an investment' to him in a way nobody not a crook would have allowed to be smoothed over and he allowed it to be smoothed over . 
Finished raving ? she inquired . 
I gave Corliss a thousand dollars , he said , slowly . 
Considering the fact that it was my last , I flatter myself it was not unhandsomely done though I may never need it . 
We do one thing in the South , where I came from . 
We protect our women This looks like it ! Keeping me when I love you , he said , his face whiter than she had ever seen it . 
I love you ! I'm your dog ! You take care of yourself if you want to take care of anybody else ! As sure as My dance , Miss Madison . 
I thought it would never come , you know but it's here at last and so am I. He laughed propitiatingly . 
Ray yielded now at once . 
She moved him aside with her gloved forearm as if he were merely an awkward stranger who unwittingly stood between her and the claiming partner . 
Carrying the gesture farther , she took the latter's arm , and smilingly , and without a backward glance , passed onward and left the gallery . 
Then without any fatiguing preamble , he proposed marriage . 
Cora did not accept , but effected a compromise , which , for the present , was to consist of an exchange of photographs and letters . 
She was having an evening to her heart . 
He was visibly making an impression . 
He caused plenty of flutter . 
Cora waited till the evening was half over before she gave him any visible attention . 
Cora gave him no greeting whatever she dismissed her former partner and carelessly turned away with Corliss to some chairs in a corner . 
Do you see that ? asked Vilas , leaning over the balcony railing with Richard Lindley . 
He doesn't dance she'll sit out with him now , till they all read the tag she's put on him . 
